{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "name": "孤沙锥", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-gallinago", "name": "沙锥属", "latinName": "Gallinago", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "沙锥属（Gallinago）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联18种鸟类，如Fuegian snipe、Jameson's snipe、林沙锥等18种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 18, "x": -2.62, "y": 495.86, "z": 43.25}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "name": "孤沙锥", "latinName": "Gallinago solitaria", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "孤沙锥（Gallinago solitaria）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如孤沙锥。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -945.43, "y": 82.83, "z": -56.49}, {"id": "bird-孤沙锥-153f0fa2", "name": "孤沙锥", "englishName": "Solitary snipe", "latinName": "Gallinago solitaria", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The solitary snipe (Gallinago solitaria) is a small stocky wader. It is found in the Palearctic from northeast Iran to Korea and Japan. Description This is a large and heavy snipe 29–31 cm long with a stocky body and relatively short legs for a wader. Its upperparts, head and neck are streaked and patterned with medium brown stripes and whitish edges to the feathers forming lines down its back. The face is whitish. The breast is ginger-brown and the belly is white with brown barring on the flanks. The brown and black bill is long, straight and fairly slender. The legs and feet are yellowish-olive to yellowish-brown. All plumages are similar, but females average larger. There are two quite similar subspecies. Nominate G. s. solitaria is very widespread. The breeding range of G. s. japonica, which is richer red and less white above, is unknown, but it winters in Japan. The solitary snipe makes a hoarse kensh call as it takes off, and has a far carrying chok-a-chok-a call when displaying. The solitary snipe has a relatively slow, heavy flight. Distribution and habitat The solitary snipe breeds discontinuously in the mountains of eastern Asia, in eastern Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Mongolia. Many birds are sedentary in the high mountains, or just move downhill in hard weather, but others are migratory, wintering in northeast Iran, Pakistan, northern India, Bangladesh, eastern China, Korea, Japan and Sakhalin. Behaviour This snipe breeds in mountain bogs and river valleys above the timberline, typically from 2,400 m to 5000 m. It is often found in similar marshes and swamps at lower altitudes when not breeding or on migration. The solitary snipe builds a saucer-shaped nest of dry grass in the drier areas of its breeding wetland. The nest is concealed in a dense tuft of grass or sedges. This bird has an aerial display, which involves flying high in circles, followed by a powerful stoop during which the bird makes a \"drumming\" sound, caused by vibrations of modified outer tail feathers. The solitary snipe forages by pushing its long bill deep into the mud seeking invertebrates, such as insects and worms, seeds and plants. It is quite approachable, but if alarmed, it crouches, and its cryptic plumage provides effective camouflage when the bird stands motionless amongst marsh vegetation. When flushed, it drops back into the marsh after a short slow flight. Images References Hayman, Marchant and Prater, Shorebirds ISBN 0-395-37903-2", "shortSummary": "The solitary snipe (Gallinago solitaria) is a small stocky wader. It is found in the Palearctic from northeast Iran to Korea and Japan.", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Solitary_Snipe_imported_from_iNaturalist_photo_252531185_on_13_June_2024.jpg/960px-Solitary_Snipe_imported_from_iNaturalist_photo_252531185_on_13_June_2024.jpg", "order": "Charadriiformes", "family": "Scolopacidae", "genus": "Gallinago", "species": "Gallinago solitaria", "orderCn": "鸻形目", "familyCn": "鹬科", "genusCn": "沙锥属", "speciesCn": "孤沙锥", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-charadriiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-scolopacidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-gallinago", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-charadriiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-scolopacidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-gallinago", "species": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria"}, "expandable": true, "x": -945.43, "y": 82.83, "z": -63.84}], "links": [{"key": "bird-孤沙锥-153f0fa2__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "source": "bird-孤沙锥-153f0fa2", "target": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-gallinago", "source": "taxonomy-species-gallinago-solitaria", "target": "taxonomy-genus-gallinago", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：孤沙锥 属于属 沙锥属。"}]}
